notes: WORLD RECORD Jayasuriya scored 50 in 17 balls beating SP O'Donnell's record of 18 balls
Sri Lanka's first wicket fell at 70, with Kaluwitharana being dismissed for 0. Jayasuriya had 66 not out and there were 4 extras.
Ata-ur-Rehman took 3 wickets in 5 balls to conclude the Sri Lanka innings. Vic Issacs, Peter Griffiths.
